(Description)
Implement the myAtoi(string s) function, which converts a string to a 32-bit signed integer.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public int myAtoi(String s) {
        int i = 0;
        int n = s.length();

        int sign = 1;
        int result = 0;

        int INT_MAX = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int INT_MIN = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        while (i < n && s.charAt(i) == ' ') {
            i++;
        }

        if (i < n && (s.charAt(i) == '+' || s.charAt(i) == '-')) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '-') {
                sign = -1;
            }

            i++;
        }

        while (i < n && Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))) {
            int digit = s.charAt(i) - '0';

            if (result > INT_MAX/10
            || (result == INT_MAX / 10 && digit > 7)) {
                return sign == 1 ? INT_MAX : INT_MIN;
            }

            result = result * 10 + digit;
            i++;
        }

        return result * sign;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
The key concept of this problem is covering all of the characters in the given String from left to the right.
According to the conditions of Atoi, while loops and if statement were generated in order.

One thing that I learned was that a number in the character was ASCII value.
Therefore, any number in characters subtracted by character 0 is going to be the integer.
